docs.summary:
Recurring payment is described by `frequency` (day, week, month) and `interval`.

 For example, to create a recurring payment every 14 days, just set `interval` to 14 and frequency to `DAY`.

 In some cases there should be a trial period for the order, after which payments start to occur.
 Trial period is also defined as `frequency` and `interval` pair.

 So one can define a monthly 'subscription' with a 14 days trial period.

members.name: trial
members.doc: trial period for recurring payment (optional)

members.name: billingCycles
members.doc:
how many billing cycles should be done before subscription finishes
 (optional, 0 by default means endless subscription)

members.doc: interval of recurring payment (required)

members.name: firstCycleStartDate
members.doc:
date in the future or in the past when the first billing cycle begins
 (the first off-session payment is performed when it ends)

members.name: frequency
members.doc: frequency of recurring payment (required)

docs.summary:
Callback URLs which are used to return buyer to third party system.

 When user clicks to pay for the order he/she is redirected to the payment page. After that (depending on the payment
 status) user is redirected to one of return URLs.

members.name: successUrl
members.doc: URL to redirect buyer in case of approved (successful) transaction (required)

members.name: errorUrl
members.doc: URL to redirect buyer in case of failed/rejected transaction (required)

members.name: cancelUrl
members.doc: URL to redirect buyer in case of buyer canceled the transaction (optional, default: `{error_url}`)

members.name: pendingUrl
members.doc:
URL to redirect buyer in case of pending transaction (that might take some time to process) (optional, default:
 `{success_url}`)

members.name: eventHook
members.doc:
Event hook which should be used (required if async payments providers are used).

 Supported values:
 * web url (starts with `https://`) - web hook, events are sent via http protocol
 * `rpc:${groupId.artifactId}` - RPC hook, webhook listener should be registered on application side as rpc service

 For more information, please read related section of [this guide][1].

  [1]: /cashier-pay/guides/Order%20overview

members.name: simpleReturnUrl
members.doc:
Simple callback url to return buyer to the third party system after redirect url will contain payment status in
 'status' query parameter.

 Examples:
 * `{complete_url}?status=approved`
 * `{complete_url}?status=pending`

members.name: supportedChargeIntents
members.doc:
Charge intents which are supported by this payment method.

 What kind of payment the buyer wants to perform: A one-time payment, a recurring payment, or an authorize
 payment - authorize is when the provider reserves the funds from the users credit card, but doesnt actually
 charge them. This is usually done for booking style flows, where the hotel reserves the booking amount but only
 charges it when the guest arrives. Authorize flow is not fully supported by Cashier yet, work in progress.

 Provider ID (like `net.authorize` or `payPal`) can be used for UI purposes.

 Checkout [PaymentProviders.scala][1] for the list of defined providers.

   [1]: https://github.com/wix-private/cashier/blob/master/payment-services/blackbeard-modules/payment-domain/src/main/scala/com/wixpress/payment/settings/PaymentProviders.scala

docs.summary:
enumeration with all possible domains Possible values are:
  • UNDEFINED
  • ORDER
  • CREDIT_CARD
  • SAVED_CREDIT_CARD
  • PAYMENT_METHOD

The type of order item Possible values are:
  • UNDEFINED
  • PHYSICAL - a physical good
  • DIGITAL - a digital good

Frequency unit of recurring payment Possible values are:
  • UNDEFINED
  • DAY
  • WEEK
  • MONTH
  • YEAR

Type of the order Possible values are:
  • UNDEFINED
  • ONE_TIME
  • SUBSCRIPTION

status of the order (more info [here][1]) [1]: /cashier-pay/guides/Order%20overview Possible values are:
  • UNDEFINED
  • INITIALIZED - meaning the order was created
  • IN_PROCESS - meaning payment process for this order has started OR has been successfully completed
  • EXPIRED - meaning payment process for this order didn't finish in time
  • NOT_APPROVED - meaning payment process has failed (due to any of the reasons)
  • APPROVED - meaning that order has been approved (has approved transaction)
  • SUBSCRIPTION_ACTIVE - meaning recurring payment is active
  • SUBSCRIPTION_CANCELLED - meaning recurring payment was cancelled by user
  • SUBSCRIPTION_FINISHED - meaning the total billing cycles for the optional trial and the regular payment periods was completed (not yet supported)
  • SUBSCRIPTION_PENDING - meaning recurring payment is not active yet, waiting for the first payment
  • SUBSCRIPTION_SUSPENDED - meaning recurring payment was suspended by user

Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN
  • REGULAR
  • EXPRESS

Possible values are:
  • SAME_WINDOW
  • NEW_WINDOW
  • EMBEDDED

Possible values are:
  • UNDEFINED
  • INITIALIZATION
  • INITIALIZED
  • IN_PROCESS
  • APPROVED
  • PENDING_MERCHANT - transaction is pending, merchant action is required
  • PENDING_BUYER - means just pending, for example transaction is pending because of fraud check
  • DECLINED
  • FAILED
  • BUYER_CANCELED
  • TIMEOUT
  • REFUND
  • CHARGE_BACK
  • OFFLINE

What kind of payment the buyer wants to perform: A one-time payment, a recurring payment, or an authorize payment - authorize is when the provider reserves the funds from the users credit card, but doesnt actually charge them. This is usually done for booking style flows, where the hotel reserves the booking amount but only charges it when the guest arrives. Authorize flow is not fully supported by Cashier yet, work in progress. Possible values are:
  • UNDEFINED
  • SALE
  • AUTHORIZATION
  • RECURRING
